<html>
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Route 2 Comply</title>
<link rel="icon" href="route2comply.jpg">
<link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">

<head>
  <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet"
    integrity="sha384-QWTKZyjpPEjISv5WaRU9OFeRpok6YctnYmDr5pNlyT2bRjXh0JMhjY6hW+ALEwIH" crossorigin="anonymous">
</head>

<body>

  <%- include('header') %>
    <%- include('main-img') %>


      <div id="content">

        <div id="info">

          <div>
            Produce audit compliance serves as a vital safeguard for the integrity of the agricultural industry, ensuring that
            sustainability, organics, and food safety standards are met consistently. Route2Comply, Inc. recognizes the paramount
            importance of these aspects and offers tailored solutions to support produce companies in their compliance efforts.
            Through proactive collaboration and expertise in audit procedures, Route2Comply aids producers in navigating the
            intricate landscape of regulations and industry guidelines. By aligning with Route2Comply, companies can enhance their
            ability to maintain the highest standards of quality and safety throughout their operations. From facilitating organic
            certification processes to implementing robust food safety protocols, Route2Comply stands as a trusted partner dedicated
            to empowering producers to achieve and exceed compliance expectations while fostering a culture of sustainability and
            excellence within the industry.
          </div>

        </div>



        <h2 id="services">Our Services </h2>
        <div class="container">
          <div class="row">
            <div class="col-lg-4 col-12">
              <div class="card">
                <div class="card-body">
                  <img src="safety.jpg" />
                  <h5 class="card-title">Audit Readiness </h5>
                  <p class="card-text"> Preparing and updating programs to run efficiently and comply with GFSI/non-GFSI
                    standards..</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-4 col-12">
              <div class="card">
                <div class="card-body">
                  <img src="usda.jpg" />
                  <h5 class="card-title"> </h5>
                  <p class="card-text">Assistance with SOE readiness, organic fraud prevention plans, and more.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="col-lg-4 col-12">
              <div class="card">
                <div class="card-body">
                  <img src="sustainability.png" />
                  <h5 class="card-title">Sustainability and/or Pollinator commitments</h5>
                  <p class="card-text">Helping companies comply with requirements from Wal-Mart, Kroger, and Whole
                    Foods,
                    and
                    others. This can involve utilizing the Sustainability Standard, PrimusGFS Module 9 - IPM, USDA
                    Organic.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <h2 id="contact">Send Us a Message </h2>


        <div class="contact-container">
          <form action="/send_email" method="post">
            <label for="email">email adress</label>
            <input type="text" id="email" name="email" placeholder="Your email..">

            <label for="name"> Name</label>
            <input type="text" id="name" name="name" placeholder="Your full name..">

            <label for="message">Subject</label>
            <textarea id="message" name="message" placeholder="Write something.." style="height:200px"></textarea>

            <input type="submit" value="Submit">
          </form>
        </div>

      </div>
</body>

</html>